Term deposits refer to an account in which money has been placed for a fixed period of time for a stated interest rate.

All deposits are to be reported net of any set-offs.
Include:
* account balances from Australian banks and non-bank financial intermediaries such as merchant banks;
* deposits from Australian banks and non-bank financial institutions;
* $A equivalent of foreign currency deposits; and
* accounts from which payments can be made to third parties - eg ATMs, debit card or another electronic device.
Exclude:
* subordinated debt issues;
* subordinated loans;
* loans due to the parent entity, controlled entities, associated entities, joint venture entities and other branches under the same parent entity;
* securities sold under agreements to repurchase;
* treasury related short-term borrowings from other banks;
* promissory notes;
* certificates of deposits;
* NOW where no cheque books are issued; and
* commercial paper.

Deposits: Transaction and non-transaction deposit accounts denominated in foreign currency. Reported in AUD equivalent.
